  "chapter": {
    "number": 26,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Song of Salvation"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "In that day this song will be sung in the land of Judah:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "We have a strong city;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "salvation is established as its walls and ramparts.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Open the gates so a righteous nation may enter—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "one that remains faithful.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will keep in perfect peace the steadfast of mind,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because he trusts in You.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Trust in the LORD forever,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because GOD the LORD is the Rock eternal.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For He has humbled those who dwell on high;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He lays the lofty city low.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He brings it down to the ground;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He casts it into the dust.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Feet trample it down—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the feet of the oppressed,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the steps of the poor.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The path of the righteous is level;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You clear a straight path for the upright.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yes, we wait for You, O LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "we walk in the path of Your judgments.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Your name and renown",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "are the desire of our souls.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My soul longs for You in the night;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "indeed, my spirit seeks You at dawn.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2600
          },
          {
            "text": "For when Your judgments come upon the earth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the people of the world learn righteousness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though grace is shown to the wicked man,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he does not learn righteousness.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "In the land of righteousness he acts unjustly",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and fails to see the majesty of the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "O LORD, Your hand is upraised,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but they do not see it.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will see Your zeal for Your people",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and be put to shame.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The fire set for Your enemies",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will consume them!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "O LORD, You will establish peace for us.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "For all that we have accomplished,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You have done for us.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "O LORD our God, other lords besides You have had dominion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but Your name alone do we confess.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The dead will not live;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the departed spirits will not rise.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Therefore You have punished and destroyed them;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You have wiped out all memory of them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have enlarged the nation, O LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You have enlarged the nation.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You have gained glory for Yourself;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You have extended all the borders of the land.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "O LORD, they sought You in their distress;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when You disciplined them, they poured out a quiet prayer.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "As a woman with child about to give birth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "writhes and cries out in pain,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so were we in Your presence, O LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "We were with child; we writhed in pain;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but we gave birth to wind.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "We have given no salvation to the earth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor brought any life into the world.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your dead will live; their bodies will rise.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Awake and sing, you who dwell in the dust!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For your dew is like the dew of the morning,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the earth will bring forth her dead.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Go, my people, enter your rooms",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and shut your doors behind you.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Hide yourselves a little while",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "until the wrath has passed.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For behold, the LORD is coming out of His dwelling",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to punish the inhabitants of the earth for their iniquity.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The earth will reveal her bloodshed",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and will no longer conceal her slain.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 2600,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or my spirit within me seeks You.",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 26,
          "verse": 9
        }
      }
    ]
  },
